1
00:00:01,660 --> 00:00:04,130
[Magic Factory]

2
00:00:07,209 --> 00:00:10,549
[Park Hae Jin]

3
00:00:12,850 --> 00:00:16,250
[Jin Ki Joo]

4
00:00:17,289 --> 00:00:19,990
[Jung Joon Ho]

5
00:00:19,990 --> 00:00:23,010
[Park Seo Yeon | Jeong Seok Yong | Ko Kyu Phil]

6
00:00:27,029 --> 00:00:31,169
[From Now On, Showtime!]

7
00:00:31,169 --> 00:00:34,669
[All characters, locations, groups, and incidents are fictional.]

8
00:00:34,669 --> 00:00:36,809
[Episode 8]

9
00:00:36,809 --> 00:00:39,140
Your total is 17,200 won.

10
00:00:45,950 --> 00:00:47,490
Sir?

11
00:00:55,859 --> 00:00:58,359
Please, I can't breathe...

12
00:01:01,729 --> 00:01:03,529
Sir?

13
00:01:04,540 --> 00:01:05,440
Sir.

14
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:08,369
- Honey, I'm here.
- Hi, Honey!

15
00:01:10,139 --> 00:01:11,809
I'm sorry.

16
00:01:11,809 --> 00:01:14,110
Have a good day!

17
00:01:16,950 --> 00:01:20,350
- I've never seen him before.
- Me neither.

18
00:01:21,319 --> 00:01:23,520
That man...

19
00:01:24,819 --> 00:01:27,929
I could tell that he was like me.

20
00:02:43,599 --> 00:02:45,540
Honey...

21
00:02:47,439 --> 00:02:49,840
The scumbag who killed me...

22
00:02:50,979 --> 00:02:53,439
The evil being who killed me...

23
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:56,249
It was him.

24
00:03:11,699 --> 00:03:16,030
I told you. I will not sell it before I die.

25
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:20,869
Honey, please.

26
00:03:20,869 --> 00:03:25,040
Will you please change your mind?

27
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:28,650
What if they hurt the kids at the orphanage to get back at you?

28
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:32,719
Let's move to a place where we can live in peace.

29
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:37,720
Right. I am doing this because I want to live in peace.

30
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:42,359
Before I met you, the children and I were always moving around.

31
00:03:42,359 --> 00:03:44,559
We'd get pushed out because of some redevelopment projects...

32
00:03:44,559 --> 00:03:47,529
or get kicked out because no one wanted an orphanage in the area.

33
00:03:47,529 --> 00:03:51,729
Every time that happened, the children and I cried together.

34
00:03:52,969 --> 00:03:55,539
I didn't want them to have to go through something like that again,

35
00:03:55,539 --> 00:03:58,610
so I worked day and night to buy that plot of land.

36
00:03:58,610 --> 00:04:01,049
So how could I sell it?

37
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:08,290
I want the kids to have a place that they can call their hometown.

38
00:04:08,919 --> 00:04:12,460
A warm home where they can always return to...

39
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:17,359
even when they're all grown up.

40
00:04:17,359 --> 00:04:19,729
That's my dream.

41
00:04:19,729 --> 00:04:21,629
Then I guess we have no choice.

42
00:04:21,629 --> 00:04:23,770
Thanks for understanding, Honey.

43
00:04:23,770 --> 00:04:27,240
I'm so glad you understand.

44
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,570
Oh, you came to pick up the document. Right?

45
00:04:29,570 --> 00:04:31,790
Hold on.

46
00:04:47,629 --> 00:04:52,040
[Food | Beverage]

47
00:05:07,979 --> 00:05:11,980
I was going to just take what I could and leave,

48
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:15,500
but what can I do? She said she couldn't sell it before she died.

49
00:05:18,389 --> 00:05:20,820
So I had to kill her.

50
00:05:24,729 --> 00:05:26,700
You see,

51
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:32,280
this is why you should've listened to me... when I asked you nicely.

52
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:48,990
He deliberately approached her because he was after her money?

53
00:05:49,789 --> 00:05:51,489
How could he do such a thing?

54
00:05:51,489 --> 00:05:53,120
He's evil.

55
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:55,059
Ms. Yoon,

56
00:05:55,059 --> 00:05:58,060
we will catch that scumbag at all costs.

57
00:05:58,060 --> 00:05:59,600
Okay.

58
00:06:00,329 --> 00:06:03,129
Didn't the police call earlier and say they caught the perp?

59
00:06:03,129 --> 00:06:06,169
Right. The baseball bat, was the murder weapon.

60
00:06:06,169 --> 00:06:08,870
They said they found it in the thugs' office.

61
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:10,940
But why...

62
00:06:12,010 --> 00:06:17,450
Right. He put it in the bag, so he must've put it there later.

63
00:06:17,450 --> 00:06:19,750
If we can prove that...

64
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:22,950
Hey, guys. Aren't you forgetting something here?

65
00:06:22,950 --> 00:06:26,289
- That's right.
- Yes, good.

66
00:06:26,289 --> 00:06:28,289
- The security footage.
- What "footage"?

67
00:06:28,289 --> 00:06:32,130
I bet the footage shows him leaving the store with the bag.

68
00:06:32,130 --> 00:06:35,429
- I'll secure the footage first.
- Okay.

69
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:38,601
When did you come back?

70
00:06:38,601 --> 00:06:41,509
Gosh, I can't believe this.

71
00:06:41,509 --> 00:06:45,279
Look at you totally ignoring me.

72
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:47,849
You guys, I am the Grim Reaper.

73
00:06:47,849 --> 00:06:49,149
Not just a reaper.

74
00:06:49,149 --> 00:06:52,479
I am the Grim Reaper who came to collect her soul!

75
00:06:52,479 --> 00:06:54,750
Well, I'm a bit of an oddball.

76
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:58,020
I've seen countless ghosts and spirits.

77
00:06:58,020 --> 00:07:01,589
The Grim Reaper isn't all that different, either.

78
00:07:02,629 --> 00:07:05,630
Fine. Then I'll just do what I came here to do.

79
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:07,070
Come on. Let's go.

80
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:10,270
Earlier, you said I'm not supposed to die until 11:30 p.m.

81
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:11,700
We still have time.

82
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,039
We have to make a few stops along the way.

83
00:07:13,039 --> 00:07:15,009
If I go back and forth, it'll be a hassle.

84
00:07:15,009 --> 00:07:16,470
Let's just leave now. Come on.

85
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:19,580
Wait! Hold on!

86
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:24,779
Other Grim Reapers... wait for three days until the funeral is over.

87
00:07:24,779 --> 00:07:27,750
- Isn't that the rule?
- Yes.

88
00:07:29,419 --> 00:07:31,820
Well, you're right. That is the rule.

89
00:07:31,820 --> 00:07:33,130
Then, what about now?

90
00:07:33,130 --> 00:07:37,159
Are you deliberately ignoring the rule for your convenience?

91
00:07:37,159 --> 00:07:39,429
No, it's not that.

92
00:07:39,429 --> 00:07:41,200
I've been swamped with work.

93
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:44,899
See? I'm so tired that I nearly lost my voice.

94
00:07:44,899 --> 00:07:47,839
Besides, other Grim Reapers also do it this way these days.

95
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:50,810
Fine. Then, even if I file an official complaint against you,

96
00:07:50,810 --> 00:07:52,779
you won't get in trouble. Right?

97
00:07:52,779 --> 00:07:54,610
A complaint?

98
00:07:55,549 --> 00:07:58,649
Gosh, this is nuts.

99
00:07:58,649 --> 00:08:01,820
You see, it's not like I want to do this.

100
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:04,789
The deceased we get these days are just clueless.

101
00:08:04,789 --> 00:08:10,089
Instead of waiting quietly for the Grim Reaper, they roam around to vent their spite.

102
00:08:10,089 --> 00:08:13,730
Do you know how many souls I've failed to collect recently?

103
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:17,870
I can wait three days, but what if they run away?

104
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:20,810
Then I'll be the one getting reprimanded.

105
00:08:20,810 --> 00:08:23,510
Calm down. You'll lose your voice.

106
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:27,910
Well, since you brought up the topic, I'll say this.

107
00:08:27,910 --> 00:08:33,279
Back in the day, people prepared a meal for the Grim Reaper,

108
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:35,689
so we'd have something to eat during the funeral.

109
00:08:35,689 --> 00:08:37,860
But it's not like that these days.

110
00:08:37,860 --> 00:08:41,959
I don't get anything! Nothing!

111
00:08:41,959 --> 00:08:44,860
Goodness. Talking about this is making me really angry.

112
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:47,599
I don't care if you file a complaint. Come on! Let's go.

113
00:08:47,599 --> 00:08:49,129
Wait!

114
00:08:49,129 --> 00:08:53,100
I'll do it.

115
00:08:53,970 --> 00:08:56,610
- Do what?
- I'll prepare a meal for you.

116
00:08:56,610 --> 00:09:00,640
I'll prepare a feast for you.

117
00:09:06,820 --> 00:09:09,250
Okay, where? Let's go.

118
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:11,320
Come on. Let's go. Which way?

119
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,019
What are you going to do?

120
00:09:13,019 --> 00:09:14,860
That was so easy.

121
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:16,690
You told me...

122
00:09:16,690 --> 00:09:17,829
that figuring out who...

123
00:09:17,829 --> 00:09:20,829
is benefiting the most would help me narrow down my list of suspects.

124
00:09:20,829 --> 00:09:22,470
Right, I did.

125
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:24,330
Lee Jonggu.

126
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:27,340
He and Ms. Yoon got married only a few months ago.

127
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:31,780
If she dies, he'll inherit all her money.

128
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:34,309
Even the orphanage and the land.

129
00:09:34,309 --> 00:09:36,849
Look at you. You sure have learned a thing or two.

130
00:09:36,849 --> 00:09:38,950
I actually looked into him already.

131
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:40,279
He was convicted of fraud in the past.

132
00:09:40,279 --> 00:09:43,029
I knew it. There's something fishy about him.

133
00:09:43,029 --> 00:09:47,360
Don't you think he should be on our list of suspects?

134
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:50,659
But it's unrelated to this case. It happened ten years ago.

135
00:09:50,659 --> 00:09:53,459
And it was a small amount, so he was let off with a fine.

136
00:09:53,459 --> 00:09:57,240
Most importantly, we have solid evidence that these punks did it.

137
00:09:57,240 --> 00:10:01,009
By any chance, do you have the entire footage?

138
00:10:01,009 --> 00:10:02,970
I do, but this case is already...

139
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:06,239
Please. Let me go through it just once more.

140
00:10:06,239 --> 00:10:10,409
Who knows? Maybe I'll spot Lee Jonggu doing something suspicious.

141
00:10:10,409 --> 00:10:13,419
Is there something you're looking for?

142
00:10:13,419 --> 00:10:15,319
Or is it just a gut feeling?

143
00:10:16,049 --> 00:10:18,559
I just want to make sure.

144
00:10:19,759 --> 00:10:22,309
This is about Ms. Yoon, you know.

145
00:10:28,829 --> 00:10:31,930
[Kangguk Supermarket]

146
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:45,720
The bag... He doesn't have it.

147
00:10:52,389 --> 00:10:54,059
This is insane.

148
00:10:54,059 --> 00:10:56,459
I can't believe he's bringing the Grim Reaper here.

149
00:10:56,459 --> 00:10:59,159
- Hurry. Let's get out of here.
- Hey, where's Areum?

150
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:02,029
- I told her not to come.
- Good.

151
00:11:02,029 --> 00:11:04,070
Technically, we're roaming ghosts too.

152
00:11:04,070 --> 00:11:06,600
If the Grim Reaper sees us, he'll take all of us.

153
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,070
Come on. Let's hurry.

154
00:11:08,070 --> 00:11:10,980
What if we run into the Grim Reaper as we're leaving the house?

155
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:14,250
Goodness. What's with all the fuss?

156
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:15,409
Adviser Choi!

157
00:11:15,409 --> 00:11:19,150
Do you think I'd let you guys get dragged away?

158
00:11:19,150 --> 00:11:22,919
Just hide behind me. I will keep you safe.

159
00:11:22,919 --> 00:11:26,090
So we can just count on you and stay home?

160
00:11:26,090 --> 00:11:30,160
That's right. I've been around for 2,000 years.

161
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:33,659
Grim Reapers are no match for me.

162
00:11:33,659 --> 00:11:35,829
You're so cool!

163
00:11:36,669 --> 00:11:39,870
I have to leave before Yoon Minsook dies.

164
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:41,570
Okay, I heard you.

165
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:47,040
What are all these ghosts doing here?

166
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:50,379
How dare you barge into...

167
00:11:52,519 --> 00:11:55,750
Geom? Aren't you Choi Geom?

168
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:58,590
- Hyeonjoon? Is it you?
- You're Geom, right?

169
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:01,559
- Hey, how long has it been?
- My gosh!

170
00:12:01,559 --> 00:12:05,289
- My goodness.
- I can't believe this!

171
00:12:05,289 --> 00:12:07,799
- It's been ages.
- Hey, hold on.

172
00:12:07,799 --> 00:12:10,370
Has it been about 2,000 years?

173
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:12,039
This is my first time running into you after I died.

174
00:12:12,039 --> 00:12:14,539
- Yes!
- It's so good to see you!

175
00:12:14,539 --> 00:12:16,470
Do you two know each other?

176
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:18,309
Yes, we grew up together.

177
00:12:18,309 --> 00:12:21,680
- It's so good to see you. My gosh.
- Hey, get up.

178
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:24,380
He and I studied under the same teacher.

179
00:12:24,380 --> 00:12:26,049
This is Shin Hyeonjoon, my childhood friend.

180
00:12:26,049 --> 00:12:29,590
- I see. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

181
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:32,220
My gosh. Come on in. It's been so long.

182
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:35,259
- Hey, this is amazing.
- How long has it been?

183
00:12:35,259 --> 00:12:37,959
Who knew we'd meet again like this? This is just amazing!

184
00:12:37,959 --> 00:12:42,029
- Oh, my.
- Hold on. You must be exhausted.

185
00:12:42,029 --> 00:12:44,600
I see that your nose has gotten even longer.

186
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:48,110
Hey, yours has gotten wider.

187
00:12:48,110 --> 00:12:51,040
You look like a goat.

188
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:53,679
- Anyway, it's so good to see you.
- Take a seat.

189
00:12:53,679 --> 00:12:55,680
- Okay.
- Go on.

190
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:58,030
Seriously, it's so good to see you.

191
00:12:58,030 --> 00:13:02,619
How did that beaky fool become the Grim Reaper?

192
00:13:05,119 --> 00:13:07,460
- (Spare me a moment.)
- (Okay.)

193
00:13:07,460 --> 00:13:10,459
Would you like something to drink?

194
00:13:10,459 --> 00:13:12,259
Just a cup of instant coffee.

195
00:13:12,259 --> 00:13:16,799
Oh, instant coffee? Make him a cup of instant coffee.

196
00:13:17,799 --> 00:13:20,969
We have brewed coffee, too.

197
00:13:20,969 --> 00:13:23,540
I said, instant coffee.

198
00:13:26,879 --> 00:13:30,649
So, you want me to help you buy some time?

199
00:13:31,379 --> 00:13:35,419
Three days would be the maximum, including the funeral.

200
00:13:35,419 --> 00:13:37,789
If it takes longer, things will get out of hand.

201
00:13:37,789 --> 00:13:39,190
Can you catch him before that?

202
00:13:39,190 --> 00:13:41,190
If Head Yoon passes away like this,

203
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:44,659
the murderer will inherit the land on which the orphanage is built on.

204
00:13:44,659 --> 00:13:47,100
Please help us.

205
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:50,829
I know how to handle that beaky fool.

206
00:13:55,210 --> 00:13:57,809
You see, I'd never do this for other ghosts.

207
00:13:57,809 --> 00:14:02,649
But since this concerns my dear friend Mr. Goat's employees,

208
00:14:02,649 --> 00:14:04,379
I'll graciously turn a blind eye to this matter.

209
00:14:04,379 --> 00:14:09,090
However, you must ascend as soon as your contract is up. Understood?

210
00:14:09,090 --> 00:14:11,650
Yes, of course.

211
00:14:12,420 --> 00:14:14,430
Thank you, my friend.

212
00:14:14,430 --> 00:14:18,359
Thank goodness the Grim Reaper is my friend.

213
00:14:18,359 --> 00:14:21,300
- I'm happy to help.
- Thanks.

214
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:23,099
You said people used to prepare a meal for you.

215
00:14:23,099 --> 00:14:26,369
I see that it consists of rice, water, pollack, soy sauce, soybean paste...

216
00:14:26,369 --> 00:14:30,009
Hey, come on! Who eats stuff like that these days?

217
00:14:30,009 --> 00:14:33,879
Can you order some rose tteokbokki?

218
00:14:33,879 --> 00:14:35,909
What? Rose tteokbokki?

219
00:14:35,909 --> 00:14:37,679
The Grim Reaper eats rose tteokbokki?

220
00:14:37,679 --> 00:14:41,619
Add some cheese, ham, and glass noodles.

221
00:14:41,619 --> 00:14:43,320
Nice. I see that you're a foodie.

222
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,860
For the tteok, we'll get half rice, half wheat.

223
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:48,460
We'll also get some seaweed rice balls and plum juice. Nice!

224
00:14:49,829 --> 00:14:53,029
- This guy knows.
- Yes.

225
00:14:53,029 --> 00:14:55,700
- I like how flexible he is.
- I know.

226
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:58,039
I ordered it. It'll be delivered soon.

227
00:14:58,039 --> 00:14:59,900
Have some fruit.

228
00:15:02,369 --> 00:15:04,979
Are you crazy?

229
00:15:04,979 --> 00:15:08,309
Would you want to eat this if you were me?

230
00:15:08,309 --> 00:15:12,820
I'm sick of apples and pears.

231
00:15:12,820 --> 00:15:13,880
Why is it peeled halfway?

232
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:17,050
Don't you have something sweeter? Shine Muscat, for example.

233
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:19,060
Yes, we do!

234
00:15:19,060 --> 00:15:21,230
- We have everything.
- Hey, take this.

235
00:15:21,230 --> 00:15:24,829
You sure have expensive taste!

236
00:15:26,399 --> 00:15:28,429
- This guy is very likable.
- I know.

237
00:15:28,429 --> 00:15:30,210
Hey, what's your name?

238
00:15:30,210 --> 00:15:32,970
I'm Ma Dongcheol. Thank you.

239
00:15:36,639 --> 00:15:39,309
We bonded while playing jegi.

240
00:15:39,309 --> 00:15:40,940
We played it all the time.

241
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:43,479
- Our sandals were always worn out.
- That's right.

242
00:15:43,479 --> 00:15:45,379
- Do you remember?
- I sure do.

243
00:15:45,379 --> 00:15:48,919
- In our neighborhood...
- Yes.

244
00:15:48,919 --> 00:15:51,750
Have some of this, too.

245
00:15:55,389 --> 00:15:57,559
Hey, are you crazy?

246
00:15:58,629 --> 00:16:01,799
Do apples and pears become something different when they're peeled?

247
00:16:01,799 --> 00:16:03,399
There are some kiwis and oranges, too.

248
00:16:03,399 --> 00:16:06,340
Take it away. You can eat it all.

249
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:10,909
You'd better not come back here again. Stay away!

250
00:16:10,909 --> 00:16:14,140
Anyway, where were we? Right. When we played jegi,

251
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:17,610
all the elders in the neighborhood gathered around to watch us.

252
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:20,750
That's right. They'd bring snacks.

253
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:23,449
And the winner ate them all.

254
00:16:23,449 --> 00:16:27,489
I believe I ate them all, most of the time.

255
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:33,259
That was because I was never greedy for food back then.

256
00:16:33,259 --> 00:16:37,470
I let you eat them all because I was never a greedy eater.

257
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:41,440
Right, Kkotbun. This is making me think of Kkotbun.

258
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,240
Kkotbun? Isn't that a woman's name?

259
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:46,340
We both had a crush on her.

260
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:48,479
We played jegi again to decide who'd tell her.

261
00:16:48,479 --> 00:16:50,350
And I lost.

262
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:53,880
Hey, did you tell her back then?

263
00:16:57,149 --> 00:17:01,430
- I did tell her, but...
- But what?

264
00:17:01,430 --> 00:17:04,929
I took Kkotbun to the little hill behind her house and...

265
00:17:04,929 --> 00:17:07,400
My gosh, where did the time go? I have to go.

266
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,070
I'm late!

267
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:11,899
You're leaving already? Stay a little longer.

268
00:17:11,899 --> 00:17:15,140
Yes, stay. Come on.

269
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:17,240
You're late anyway, so just play hooky.

270
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:20,210
You just need to collect her soul within three days, right?

271
00:17:20,210 --> 00:17:22,209
If she dies today, you have to wait.

272
00:17:22,209 --> 00:17:24,779
If she dies in two days, you can take her right away. Isn't it the same thing?

273
00:17:24,779 --> 00:17:27,580
No, it's not. She must die when she's supposed to die.

274
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:29,520
Otherwise, I'll be reprimanded again.

275
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:33,890
Anyway, it was so good to see you. I'm off.

276
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:35,889
- Hey.
- Bye.

277
00:17:35,889 --> 00:17:38,530
- Bye.
- Wait, Hyeonjoon.

278
00:17:38,530 --> 00:17:41,030
I just called Domisol Pizza and placed an order.

279
00:17:41,030 --> 00:17:42,700
The Quattro combo.

280
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:47,500
With cheese?

281
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:51,270
The cheese crust with double sweet potato mousse.

282
00:17:53,779 --> 00:17:55,609
[1 Day Before Yoon Minsook's Departure to the Afterlife]

283
00:17:55,609 --> 00:17:57,149
[Kangguk Hospital]

284
00:17:57,149 --> 00:17:58,980
[Get well soon, Mom.]

285
00:17:58,980 --> 00:18:00,880
[I miss you, Mom.]

286
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:14,060
I can't die. My sweet angels need me.

287
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:18,070
What will they do if I die?

288
00:18:19,270 --> 00:18:21,369
For the children's sake,

289
00:18:21,369 --> 00:18:25,710
we must find solid evidence that Lee Jonggu is the culprit.

290
00:18:25,710 --> 00:18:28,650
One of my employees is tailing him at the moment.

291
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:33,110
He's already planning a night out with a friend, offering to treat him.

292
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:36,419
That scumbag.

293
00:18:36,419 --> 00:18:38,219
He's a piece of trash.

294
00:18:38,219 --> 00:18:44,029
You just watch. I will drag that jerk... to the afterlife with me.

295
00:18:44,029 --> 00:18:45,830
Gosh, calm down.

296
00:18:45,830 --> 00:18:47,800
You're still tied to your body.

297
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:50,800
If you leave and lose the connection, you'll really die.

298
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:55,969
Gosh, I can't believe this.

299
00:18:57,170 --> 00:18:58,879
The problem is that...

300
00:18:58,879 --> 00:19:03,349
the security footage doesn't show him leaving with the bag.

301
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:08,490
He left empty-handed. And they never found the bag at the store.

302
00:19:08,490 --> 00:19:10,119
Maybe you were mistaken.

303
00:19:10,119 --> 00:19:12,219
No, I saw it.

304
00:19:12,219 --> 00:19:14,929
It was a huge bag.

305
00:19:14,929 --> 00:19:16,830
What happened?

306
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:20,699
The baseball bat somehow disappeared from the store...

307
00:19:20,699 --> 00:19:24,330
and was magically moved to the thugs' office?

308
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:27,480
It makes no sense. It's not like it was teleported there.

309
00:19:28,469 --> 00:19:31,409
That's it, teleportation.

310
00:19:31,409 --> 00:19:36,010
I always... keep this knife in here.

311
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:37,450
Could you hold this? Thank you.

312
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:39,279
May I borrow your phone for a moment?

313
00:19:39,279 --> 00:19:42,189
A magic trick where an object is secretly moved...

314
00:19:42,189 --> 00:19:46,459
while the audience is distracted is called "misdirection."

315
00:19:52,129 --> 00:19:55,400
If Lee Jonggu used such a trick...

316
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,530
there's only one method.

317
00:19:58,940 --> 00:20:01,469
He has an accomplice.

318
00:20:27,230 --> 00:20:30,730
I was going to just take what I could and leave,

319
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:35,140
but what can I do? She said she couldn't sell it before she died.

320
00:20:35,140 --> 00:20:37,269
So I had to kill her.

321
00:20:42,779 --> 00:20:46,380
You see, this is why you should've listened to me...

322
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:49,489
when I asked you nicely.

323
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:58,390
That means...

324
00:20:59,060 --> 00:21:02,430
he somehow sneaked the bag out from here.

325
00:21:09,770 --> 00:21:11,709
There's a window here.

326
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:19,380
If he passes the bag through it...

327
00:21:19,380 --> 00:21:22,820
...the accomplice waiting will take it with him.

328
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:31,059
As expected, they used a blind spot from the surveillance cameras.

329
00:21:36,830 --> 00:21:39,900
Old lady, you're dead meat today.

330
00:21:41,940 --> 00:21:45,979
Woman! Where are you hiding?

331
00:21:45,979 --> 00:21:49,109
Lee Jonggu made sure he got caught on camera.

332
00:21:49,109 --> 00:21:52,279
To show he left empty-handed.

333
00:21:52,279 --> 00:21:54,920
And that's when the thugs barged in.

334
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:57,870
The perfect timing to be accused as the suspects.

335
00:22:00,719 --> 00:22:04,829
And so, the accomplice hid the weapon...

336
00:22:04,829 --> 00:22:07,179
in the empty thugs' office.

337
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:11,900
Isn't that friend he's meeting up with today his accomplice? To celebrate.

338
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:14,810
Then, how did he manage to get into the thugs' office?

339
00:22:14,810 --> 00:22:17,410
And how did he know it'd be empty at that hour?

340
00:22:17,410 --> 00:22:21,479
Maybe a thug from the inside could have helped them.

341
00:22:21,479 --> 00:22:24,210
Let's split up and investigate.

342
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:27,420
Areum is tailing Lee Jonggu, so I'll join her.

343
00:22:27,420 --> 00:22:29,450
Director Ma's in charge of the thugs.

344
00:22:29,450 --> 00:22:34,159
Then I'll look into the surveillance cameras... along the route from the supermarket to the office.

345
00:22:34,159 --> 00:22:36,289
Have Chief Nam tag along.

346
00:22:36,289 --> 00:22:38,700
Areum wants you to have this.

347
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:41,500
It's an earphone version of the GI speaker.

348
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:44,000
She's skilled.

349
00:22:44,670 --> 00:22:46,269
What about the Grim Reaper?

350
00:22:46,269 --> 00:22:48,809
He won't take Minsook away while we're gone, will he?

351
00:22:48,809 --> 00:22:51,880
Don't worry about him.

352
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:54,639
Adviser Choi is taking great care of him.

353
00:22:54,639 --> 00:22:57,820
- Hey!
- Stop it! Let me go!

354
00:22:57,820 --> 00:22:59,050
It's really a fun!

355
00:22:59,050 --> 00:23:01,280
- What is?
- Let's ride it just once.

356
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:03,919
Didn't we stuff ourselves with food until late last night?

357
00:23:03,919 --> 00:23:06,359
I have to go now.

358
00:23:06,359 --> 00:23:08,890
I'm late. It's time for me to work.

359
00:23:08,890 --> 00:23:12,960
Gosh, look at you. You've turned into a workaholic.

360
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:15,699
Workaholic? I'm not. I'm just doing my best.

361
00:23:15,699 --> 00:23:20,869
Hey, your 2000-year-long friend wants to make memories with you.

362
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,710
Things like this never existed back in our days, did they?

363
00:23:23,710 --> 00:23:28,909
All we did was toss sticks and play jegi... or jwibullori.

364
00:23:28,909 --> 00:23:32,119
Well, that's true.

365
00:23:32,119 --> 00:23:34,720
Time has changed now.

366
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:37,619
Even Grim Reapers should enjoy the privilege.

367
00:23:37,619 --> 00:23:41,060
You've never ridden that, have you?

368
00:23:41,060 --> 00:23:45,500
No. But I've been on the boat across the afterlife river.

369
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,859
Don't compare that to this.

370
00:23:46,859 --> 00:23:50,269
This is on a whole different level from that old boat.

371
00:23:50,269 --> 00:23:54,269
It'll help you relieve all that stress from work.

372
00:23:54,269 --> 00:23:55,409
Let's go.

373
00:23:55,409 --> 00:23:58,270
- Come here.
- But I shouldn't!

374
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:14,220
No, don't!

375
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:16,730
- Amazing, right?
- This is great.

376
00:24:16,730 --> 00:24:20,400
Keep in mind your work-life balance.

377
00:24:28,739 --> 00:24:32,380
It's fun, right, Shin Hyeonjoon?

378
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:33,979
Do you like it or not?

379
00:24:33,979 --> 00:24:36,050
Do you like it or not? Answer me!

380
00:24:37,009 --> 00:24:39,479
Do you like it or not?

381
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:43,189
You haven't answered me yet!

382
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:46,559
I'm loving it!

383
00:24:46,559 --> 00:24:48,219
This is great.

384
00:24:48,219 --> 00:24:51,630
Let me ride it one more time. It's terrific.

385
00:24:51,630 --> 00:24:55,130
- Just one more time.
- Sure, go ahead.

386
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:56,670
Don't you have a job to do?

387
00:24:56,670 --> 00:24:58,899
Why are you wasting your time?

388
00:24:58,899 --> 00:25:00,670
Something's off about it.

389
00:25:00,670 --> 00:25:02,840
The suspects flatly deny their crime,

390
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:04,539
but the evidence was at the scene in plain sight.

391
00:25:04,539 --> 00:25:07,439
That's because they're stupid.

392
00:25:07,439 --> 00:25:09,709
If you're that free, dig into a bigger case.

393
00:25:09,709 --> 00:25:11,920
This case might get out of hand.

394
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:13,220
Even Sooma Construction is involved.

395
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:17,060
Just do what you're told to do.

396
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:20,061
And... who told you to cancel...

397
00:25:20,061 --> 00:25:22,490
the blind date with Assemblyman Cho's daughter?

398
00:25:22,490 --> 00:25:23,789
I never asked for it.

399
00:25:23,789 --> 00:25:25,500
Heesoo!

400
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:29,370
When will you realize this is all for you?

401
00:25:29,370 --> 00:25:32,069
I know. I really do.

402
00:25:32,069 --> 00:25:34,869
You will reach a much higher position than me.

403
00:25:34,869 --> 00:25:37,140
So, please! I beg you!

404
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:39,939
Trust me and follow the path I've paved for you

405
00:25:39,939 --> 00:25:41,710
before you regret it later.

406
00:25:41,710 --> 00:25:43,779
That position.

407
00:25:43,779 --> 00:25:46,350
It's not where I want to reach.

408
00:25:46,350 --> 00:25:49,089
How dare you, jerk.

409
00:25:49,089 --> 00:25:52,390
Shouldn't you help your father accomplish something big?

410
00:25:52,390 --> 00:25:54,460
But why do you keep poking around and ruining things?

411
00:25:54,460 --> 00:25:56,760
And it's Sooma Construction this time!

412
00:25:57,459 --> 00:25:58,959
Excuse me?

413
00:25:58,959 --> 00:26:01,899
Forget it.

414
00:26:01,899 --> 00:26:04,099
I'm busy,

415
00:26:04,099 --> 00:26:05,770
so leave.

416
00:26:06,769 --> 00:26:09,809
Don't do anything unnecessary.

417
00:26:09,809 --> 00:26:11,310
Okay.

418
00:26:11,310 --> 00:26:14,639
[Chief Seo Changho]

419
00:26:19,580 --> 00:26:23,749
Goodness, you're something.

420
00:26:23,749 --> 00:26:26,060
You've got your golden years ahead of you.

421
00:26:26,060 --> 00:26:28,019
I told you how everyone gets one shot at life.

422
00:26:28,019 --> 00:26:33,329
Just you wait. I'm going to start a big business soon.

423
00:26:33,329 --> 00:26:36,069
- When?
- After I sell that orphanage.

424
00:26:36,069 --> 00:26:41,569
The day that the old hag dies... is when the contract is signed.

425
00:26:44,809 --> 00:26:47,279
I've got to play it safe until then.

426
00:26:47,279 --> 00:26:51,250
I brought cash today to not leave any credit card history behind.

427
00:26:51,250 --> 00:26:53,119
You meticulous jerk.

428
00:26:53,119 --> 00:26:54,049
[Areum]

429
00:26:54,049 --> 00:26:56,619
You heard that, right, Mr. Cha? I'm leaving now.

430
00:26:56,619 --> 00:26:58,690
Yes. Good job, Areum.

431
00:27:00,459 --> 00:27:01,959
[Go Seulhae]

432
00:27:01,959 --> 00:27:04,260
[Go Seulhae, Voice Recording]

433
00:27:04,260 --> 00:27:05,330
[Voice Recording]

434
00:27:07,030 --> 00:27:08,230
[Bakery]

435
00:27:08,230 --> 00:27:10,229
Let's check this place.

436
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:18,140
Are there any other surveillance cameras?

437
00:27:18,140 --> 00:27:20,380
[Real Estate]

438
00:27:20,380 --> 00:27:22,780
- The right.
- Okay, the right.

439
00:27:22,780 --> 00:27:24,480
Go in first.

440
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:27,519
- He's not here.
- He's not.

441
00:27:29,090 --> 00:27:30,350
How can he not be in any of the footage?

442
00:27:30,350 --> 00:27:34,619
We've been to over ten places, but no one looked suspicious.

443
00:27:34,619 --> 00:27:37,359
We've looked into every road now.

444
00:27:40,900 --> 00:27:44,400
Officer Go, there's another road down that side.

445
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:47,140
What? But we've been to all the roads to the office.

446
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:48,810
I was a package delivery man during my lifetime,

447
00:27:48,810 --> 00:27:51,709
so I know roads that others don't. Follow me.

448
00:27:51,709 --> 00:27:53,680
What? How?

449
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:54,879
I can't see you!

450
00:27:54,879 --> 00:27:56,549
- Excuse me!
- My bad, Officer Go.

451
00:27:56,549 --> 00:27:59,820
This is more confusing than I thought. Okay, turn around.

452
00:27:59,820 --> 00:28:01,179
- Turn around.
- Yes.

453
00:28:01,179 --> 00:28:05,259
We're going to head straight, then turn left in that alley.

454
00:28:05,259 --> 00:28:07,890
- Got it? Go!
- Yes.

455
00:28:07,890 --> 00:28:09,390
- I'm going straight now.
- Yes.

456
00:28:09,390 --> 00:28:12,199
- You're next to me, right?
- Yes.

457
00:28:12,199 --> 00:28:14,230
- Turn left.
- "Turn left."

458
00:28:14,230 --> 00:28:15,599
What?

459
00:28:16,369 --> 00:28:18,269
Senior!

460
00:28:18,269 --> 00:28:19,540
Seulhae?

461
00:28:19,540 --> 00:28:21,939
What's with him?

462
00:28:21,939 --> 00:28:23,340
Did you guys plan to meet up?

463
00:28:23,340 --> 00:28:25,110
No.

464
00:28:25,979 --> 00:28:28,180
After I sell that orphanage.

465
00:28:28,180 --> 00:28:32,449
The day that the old hag dies... is when the contract is signed.

466
00:28:32,449 --> 00:28:34,750
[Voice Recording File]

467
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:38,859
I brought cash today to not leave any credit card history behind.

468
00:28:38,859 --> 00:28:41,559
I went for lunch when they were sitting next to me.

469
00:28:41,559 --> 00:28:43,589
That can't be direct evidence of murder,

470
00:28:43,589 --> 00:28:46,459
but it's clear Lee Jonggu had the motive to kill her.

471
00:28:46,459 --> 00:28:49,230
And he surely could have worked with an accomplice.

472
00:28:49,230 --> 00:28:51,500
If only we could catch that accomplice.

473
00:28:51,500 --> 00:28:54,400
But there aren't any surveillance cameras near the thugs' office.

474
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:56,210
There weren't any in that alley, right?

475
00:28:56,210 --> 00:28:57,609
No.

476
00:28:57,609 --> 00:28:59,680
We still got an estimate of when the crime took place.

477
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:03,609
Let's look at every dashcam of the buses that passed by the office.

478
00:29:03,609 --> 00:29:05,079
Plus, Lee Jonggu's call records.

479
00:29:05,079 --> 00:29:08,949
Okay, Senior. This punk is the culprit.

480
00:29:10,219 --> 00:29:12,390
But leave room for doubt.

481
00:29:12,390 --> 00:29:17,289
Being suspicious... yet maintaining levelheadedness is crucial.

482
00:29:17,289 --> 00:29:19,229
Understood.

483
00:29:20,959 --> 00:29:25,000
Let's wrap this case up quickly and go on our date this weekend.

484
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:27,670
- Date?
- Yes.

485
00:29:27,670 --> 00:29:30,170
Didn't we promise to go bowling?

486
00:29:32,140 --> 00:29:34,780
I see. So that's a date.

487
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:37,010
Oh, you.

488
00:29:41,649 --> 00:29:43,020
What was that?

489
00:29:43,020 --> 00:29:45,419
The garbage bin is over there. It hit him, you know?

490
00:29:45,419 --> 00:29:49,660
Sorry. I was aiming for the bin, but my hand slipped.

491
00:29:55,829 --> 00:29:58,670
Ms. Cheon! Over here!

492
00:29:58,670 --> 00:30:01,669
What? Why are you alone?

493
00:30:01,669 --> 00:30:03,740
Two people are on patrol today.

494
00:30:03,740 --> 00:30:05,510
You and me.

495
00:30:05,510 --> 00:30:06,580
What?

496
00:30:07,580 --> 00:30:09,879
- So Chawoong is not coming?
- No.

497
00:30:09,879 --> 00:30:12,719
For real?

498
00:30:14,020 --> 00:30:16,690
I should go home today.

499
00:30:16,690 --> 00:30:18,759
See you next time.

500
00:30:18,759 --> 00:30:22,060
Where are you going? You've got to make the rounds.

501
00:30:22,060 --> 00:30:25,159
This is a duty of the civil police unit.

502
00:30:25,159 --> 00:30:26,959
Who came up with the patrol teams?

503
00:30:26,959 --> 00:30:29,569
Officer Go.

504
00:30:30,699 --> 00:30:35,469
There's not a single thing I like about that wench officer.

505
00:30:35,469 --> 00:30:39,440
She does everything as she pleases. Darn it!

506
00:30:50,850 --> 00:30:54,190
I have a question, Ms. Cheon.

507
00:30:54,190 --> 00:30:55,389
What is it?

508
00:30:55,389 --> 00:30:59,000
I'm a better guy than you think.

509
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:05,870
Kind, sincere, righteous, and quite cute.

510
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:12,440
So what else should I do to appeal more?

511
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:14,510
That one punch.

512
00:31:14,510 --> 00:31:18,009
"One punch?" Then it'd be money.

513
00:31:18,009 --> 00:31:20,180
Are you rich?

514
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:22,420
I'm still on probation.

515
00:31:22,420 --> 00:31:26,290
- But I'm a civil servant, so my future is stable and...
- No.

516
00:31:26,290 --> 00:31:27,889
Why don't you become a singer instead?

517
00:31:27,889 --> 00:31:30,589
You were good at singing trot back then.

518
00:31:30,589 --> 00:31:33,259
Try out for an audition show.

519
00:31:33,259 --> 00:31:36,270
You'll make it into the top seven.

520
00:31:36,270 --> 00:31:38,420
Can you see things like that?

521
00:31:44,810 --> 00:31:48,410
You've got that trot-vibe in your soul. I can feel it.

522
00:31:48,410 --> 00:31:51,579
Choose that path and you'll earn buckets.

523
00:31:51,579 --> 00:31:54,679
Do you think she will like it, too?

524
00:31:54,679 --> 00:31:56,150
Who?

525
00:31:56,990 --> 00:32:00,219
You mean that sly wench?

526
00:32:00,219 --> 00:32:02,930
What's so good about her?

527
00:32:02,930 --> 00:32:05,089
There's no reason to not like her.

528
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:09,629
She's cute, pretty, competent,

529
00:32:09,629 --> 00:32:15,370
smart, and overflowing with charm.

530
00:32:15,370 --> 00:32:17,039
Hold it.

531
00:32:18,209 --> 00:32:21,239
Do you like me?

532
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:24,249
- How did you know?
- It's obviously me, isn't it?

533
00:32:24,249 --> 00:32:28,420
I'm the only one who fits all that criteria.

534
00:32:28,420 --> 00:32:31,750
To be frank, I fell in love with you at first sight.

535
00:32:31,750 --> 00:32:34,859
- How about we get to know...
- No, thanks.

536
00:32:34,859 --> 00:32:39,659
How can you... Me? Unbelievable.

537
00:32:48,699 --> 00:32:52,340
Hey, I'm working my ass off here to clear your false charges.

538
00:32:52,340 --> 00:32:55,080
And here you are, falling asleep.

539
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:57,579
Goodness, look at this face.

540
00:33:07,460 --> 00:33:08,959
You jerk!

541
00:33:08,959 --> 00:33:10,490
You slapped me just now, didn't you?

542
00:33:10,490 --> 00:33:13,629
No way. I'm innocent.

543
00:33:13,629 --> 00:33:16,699
You always make the wrong guess and look how we ended up.

544
00:33:16,699 --> 00:33:18,939
Have you gone nuts, punk?

545
00:33:18,939 --> 00:33:22,139
This wouldn't have happened if only you hadn't gotten blood...

546
00:33:22,139 --> 00:33:23,570
on the baseball bat.

547
00:33:23,570 --> 00:33:25,909
It's not mine!

548
00:33:25,909 --> 00:33:29,209
And you're the one who told me to take the bat to the supermarket.

549
00:33:29,209 --> 00:33:32,750
Well, Big Foot... only ordered me to threaten her...

550
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:35,750
Big Foot or Dog Foot, whatever his name is,

551
00:33:35,750 --> 00:33:38,320
made things even more complicated. Darn it.

552
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:41,960
Big Foot? Does he mean that Big Foot?

553
00:33:46,459 --> 00:33:49,330
Captain, aren't you going home?

554
00:33:49,330 --> 00:33:51,080
Detective An, a minute, please?

555
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:55,639
Any thoughts about him?

556
00:33:57,840 --> 00:33:59,010
He's just a delivery man.

557
00:33:59,010 --> 00:34:00,879
Right? Nothing special, right?

558
00:34:00,879 --> 00:34:03,209
Are you looking for something? Should I help?

559
00:34:03,209 --> 00:34:05,410
No, it's okay. Go home first.

560
00:34:05,410 --> 00:34:07,850
Gosh, give yourself a break, Captain Seo.

561
00:34:07,850 --> 00:34:10,290
You won't get much from working so hard.

562
00:34:10,290 --> 00:34:13,120
- Bye.
- Let's go.

563
00:34:25,199 --> 00:34:28,070
A delivery man no one would suspect.

564
00:34:28,670 --> 00:34:30,440
It's a safe choice.

565
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:34,839
Big Foot? Do you know him?

566
00:34:34,839 --> 00:34:37,610
Yes, he was in the group Badger.

567
00:34:37,610 --> 00:34:39,449
He was with us for a year or two...

568
00:34:39,449 --> 00:34:42,290
until Sooma Construction scouted him.

569
00:34:42,290 --> 00:34:45,790
I bet he was the cleaner taking care of the dirty businesses even there.

570
00:34:45,790 --> 00:34:48,190
That's some information from you, Director Ma.

571
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:50,989
The fact that you were a thug does help at times.

572
00:34:50,989 --> 00:34:57,630
I didn't make a name nationwide, but I made a name in Kangguk.

573
00:34:57,630 --> 00:35:02,069
Sooma Construction needed land, and Lee Jonggu wanted money.

574
00:35:02,069 --> 00:35:05,409
So Minsook was an obstacle to both sides.

575
00:35:05,409 --> 00:35:08,080
Judging by the time and the tool set up,

576
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:10,049
Big Foot is surely the accomplice.

577
00:35:10,049 --> 00:35:12,580
But the problem is that we don't have any evidence.

578
00:35:12,580 --> 00:35:14,219
The Criminal Procedure Act...

579
00:35:14,219 --> 00:35:16,190
does not allow the defendant's confession...

580
00:35:16,190 --> 00:35:18,589
as proof of guilt when it is the only evidence...

581
00:35:18,589 --> 00:35:20,259
to prevent the investigative agency...

582
00:35:20,259 --> 00:35:23,290
from gaining false confessions in a coercive way.

583
00:35:23,290 --> 00:35:25,630
So corroborating evidence is necessary.

584
00:35:25,630 --> 00:35:28,429
But if both accomplices confess,

585
00:35:28,429 --> 00:35:31,469
it becomes corroborating evidence for each party,

586
00:35:31,469 --> 00:35:34,239
so no other evidence is needed.

587
00:35:34,239 --> 00:35:35,869
How about we make use of this?

588
00:35:35,869 --> 00:35:39,409
Amazing. What does that mean?

589
00:35:39,409 --> 00:35:41,679
It just means they have to own up at the same time.

590
00:35:41,679 --> 00:35:43,880
Isn't that also easier said than done?

591
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:47,080
How is that hard? Make them fight each other.

592
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:50,589
Those thugs came clean like that earlier.

593
00:35:50,589 --> 00:35:52,360
But how do we get them to meet up?

594
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:55,259
We can only make them fight or whatnot when they do.

595
00:35:55,259 --> 00:35:56,830
You're right.

596
00:35:56,830 --> 00:36:00,860
Lee Jonggu will make a move only after Minsook passes away.

597
00:36:01,500 --> 00:36:03,600
Hyeonjoon, we're almost there. Come on.

598
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:05,869
- Your legs have turned into jelly.
- Gosh.

599
00:36:05,869 --> 00:36:07,940
Wait a second.

600
00:36:07,940 --> 00:36:09,809
What do you think?

601
00:36:09,809 --> 00:36:12,980
The air feels different even from up here, right?

602
00:36:12,980 --> 00:36:16,010
It sure is nice, but what time is it?

603
00:36:16,679 --> 00:36:20,549
It's three in the morning! Three!

604
00:36:20,549 --> 00:36:22,949
You've been dragging me to places all day long.

605
00:36:22,949 --> 00:36:24,449
Let's go down now.

606
00:36:24,449 --> 00:36:26,920
I'm dead tired.

607
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:28,460
Goodness, my friend.

608
00:36:28,460 --> 00:36:30,889
Turn back when we've come all the way to Mount Nam?

609
00:36:30,889 --> 00:36:32,799
Nonsense!

610
00:36:32,799 --> 00:36:37,169
What more do you want us to do?

611
00:36:41,270 --> 00:36:45,809
- Hanging our love lock is a given, isn't it, pal?
- Love lock?

612
00:36:45,809 --> 00:36:48,479
It's for our eternal friendship.

613
00:36:48,479 --> 00:36:51,179
For our friendship. Of course, we should hang it.

614
00:36:51,179 --> 00:36:52,580
- Love lock.
- Let's go.

615
00:36:52,580 --> 00:36:54,350
- We're almost there. See that?
- We are?

616
00:36:54,350 --> 00:36:56,619
- Love lock is a must.
- Of course.

617
00:36:56,619 --> 00:36:58,650
I'm finally doing it.

618
00:36:58,650 --> 00:37:00,290
[The Day Yoon Minsook Passes Away]

619
00:37:00,290 --> 00:37:01,960
[Kangguk Hospital]

620
00:37:05,489 --> 00:37:07,329
Darn it.

621
00:37:17,810 --> 00:37:21,510
What? What's happening?

622
00:37:21,510 --> 00:37:24,449
Anyone? Help!

623
00:37:26,150 --> 00:37:27,520
Doctor!

624
00:37:34,819 --> 00:37:37,089
Doctor, what's going on?

625
00:37:45,770 --> 00:37:52,239
On January 19, 2022, 11:10 a.m,

626
00:37:52,239 --> 00:37:55,080
Ms. Yoon Minsook has passed away.

627
00:37:57,909 --> 00:37:59,480
Honey?

628
00:38:03,989 --> 00:38:07,259
Honey, wake up! Honey!

629
00:38:08,219 --> 00:38:12,429
Honey, how can you leave me behind?

630
00:38:13,159 --> 00:38:14,960
Honey!

631
00:38:24,969 --> 00:38:26,610
Honey.

632
00:38:27,739 --> 00:38:29,540
Honey!

633
00:38:35,619 --> 00:38:38,520
It's me. She's dead.

634
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:42,290
Yes, she's gone.

635
00:38:42,290 --> 00:38:45,860
We'd better sign the contract today. Where should we meet?

636
00:38:45,860 --> 00:38:50,269
Motel Jin? Okay. See you soon.

637
00:38:55,670 --> 00:39:00,179
- He's on the move right away.
- That jerk. Let's hurry.

638
00:39:04,479 --> 00:39:06,980
Isn't she breathing?

639
00:39:06,980 --> 00:39:10,650
No way. We even called her dead.

640
00:39:13,190 --> 00:39:14,759
- Oh, my gosh!
- What?

641
00:39:14,759 --> 00:39:17,259
How did this happen?

642
00:39:17,259 --> 00:39:19,430
Doctor!

643
00:39:21,830 --> 00:39:24,600
Mr. Cha, they fooled us.

644
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:26,799
So shouldn't we return the favor?

645
00:39:26,799 --> 00:39:28,969
- How?
- Misdirection.

646
00:39:28,969 --> 00:39:32,169
Don't we have the zombie tools we used at our Halloween concert?

647
00:39:38,279 --> 00:39:40,679
We'll use colored contacts for pupil response...

648
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:47,260
and silicone flesh for the carotid pulse.

649
00:39:47,860 --> 00:39:49,290
Doctor, what's going on?

650
00:39:49,290 --> 00:39:52,630
And my invisible hands can jam his stethoscope.

651
00:40:05,670 --> 00:40:10,050
But I'm sure she had no vital signs.

652
00:40:10,050 --> 00:40:12,979
It's zombie time.

653
00:40:26,799 --> 00:40:30,210
Wait. What the... Oh, no.

654
00:40:30,210 --> 00:40:31,360
Where do you think you're going?

655
00:40:31,369 --> 00:40:33,440
- I must go.
- At least stay for breakfast.

656
00:40:33,440 --> 00:40:34,699
- I really must go.
- Hang on.

657
00:40:34,699 --> 00:40:37,410
I must collect her soul.

658
00:40:37,410 --> 00:40:40,880
It only has to be done by the end of today.

659
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:45,349
It's not like it'll take you half a day... to eat your breakfast.

660
00:40:45,349 --> 00:40:49,950
Impatience has always been your downfall.

661
00:40:50,989 --> 00:40:52,589
What?

662
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:57,360
I wasn't going to say this,

663
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:59,460
but that time with Kkotbun...

664
00:40:59,460 --> 00:41:03,469
You had never held a girl's hand before... even though you were 15...

665
00:41:03,469 --> 00:41:05,500
which is why I let you win our wager out of pity.

666
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:09,670
If it were me, I would've washed up and changed my clothes first.

667
00:41:09,670 --> 00:41:11,570
You were too excited to care and declared your love for her...

668
00:41:11,570 --> 00:41:13,310
looking like a dumpster diver.

669
00:41:13,310 --> 00:41:16,110
How could anything come out of it?

670
00:41:17,150 --> 00:41:19,110
I washed up, you know.

671
00:41:19,110 --> 00:41:21,479
I washed my face!

672
00:41:22,489 --> 00:41:29,560
Also, what's this about you letting me win?

673
00:41:30,230 --> 00:41:33,030
Back in the day, Kkotbun wasn't the only one...

674
00:41:33,030 --> 00:41:35,760
who gave me googly eyes.

675
00:41:35,760 --> 00:41:38,469
- Unbelievable.
- So my heart wasn't fully in it.

676
00:41:38,469 --> 00:41:41,240
I wasn't as desperate as a certain someone.

677
00:41:41,240 --> 00:41:44,039
What the... What a joke.

678
00:41:44,039 --> 00:41:45,510
I remember it like it was yesterday.

679
00:41:45,510 --> 00:41:47,580
You were just as desperate.

680
00:41:47,580 --> 00:41:49,780
It was as if your life depended on it.

681
00:41:51,050 --> 00:41:55,380
Sure. Think that way if it puts you at ease.

682
00:41:55,380 --> 00:41:59,150
Whatever satisfies you.

683
00:42:00,659 --> 00:42:01,820
You obnoxious jerk.

684
00:42:01,820 --> 00:42:06,730
Do you consider me beneath you just because...

685
00:42:06,730 --> 00:42:09,430
you were popular with the girls?

686
00:42:25,610 --> 00:42:27,860
I dare you to accept a rematch.

687
00:42:29,750 --> 00:42:31,219
Fine.

688
00:42:32,719 --> 00:42:34,159
I'm in.

689
00:42:41,259 --> 00:42:43,099
Those letters are too small for me to read.

690
00:42:43,099 --> 00:42:45,900
You should've consumed lutein supplements... while you had the chance.

691
00:42:45,900 --> 00:42:47,300
Right here.

692
00:42:47,300 --> 00:42:50,409
Room 809. The registration is under Lee Jonggu's name.

693
00:42:50,409 --> 00:42:52,940
Is Room 810 available?

694
00:42:52,940 --> 00:42:54,409
That's the one I'd like.

695
00:42:54,409 --> 00:42:57,449
It is, but it's our suite.

696
00:42:57,449 --> 00:43:00,580
- How much a night?
- It's 3,000 dollars.

697
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:03,989
- I'll take it.
- Sure.

698
00:43:06,319 --> 00:43:08,360
Are you sure? She said 3,000 dollars.

699
00:43:08,360 --> 00:43:10,530
Appeasing Ms. Yoon's soul is worth more than that.

700
00:43:10,530 --> 00:43:13,299
- Here you go.
- Do they offer any discounts?

701
00:43:13,299 --> 00:43:15,330
Thank you.

702
00:43:20,969 --> 00:43:23,969
Set up the cameras first... and wait for further instruction.

703
00:43:23,969 --> 00:43:24,970
Okay.

704
00:43:24,970 --> 00:43:27,280
It's nervous to operate just by ourselves though.

705
00:43:27,280 --> 00:43:31,179
We'll be watching, so don't worry.

706
00:43:31,179 --> 00:43:33,680
- Shall we?
- Sure.

707
00:43:37,090 --> 00:43:38,820
We have footage.

708
00:43:38,820 --> 00:43:41,820
Mr. Cha, are you receiving?

709
00:43:41,820 --> 00:43:44,090
I can see you,

710
00:43:44,090 --> 00:43:45,529
but the audio is spotty.

711
00:43:45,529 --> 00:43:47,260
What?

712
00:43:47,260 --> 00:43:49,159
I can't hear you properly.

713
00:43:49,159 --> 00:43:53,869
Mr. Cha, why don't you... move around a little?

714
00:43:53,869 --> 00:43:57,170
Sure. Just a second.

715
00:43:57,170 --> 00:43:58,920
Are you getting this?

716
00:44:02,179 --> 00:44:03,879
Do you hear me, Mr. Nam?

717
00:44:07,320 --> 00:44:09,120
Mr. Ma?

718
00:44:11,449 --> 00:44:12,820
Do you hear me?

719
00:44:14,020 --> 00:44:15,560
Mr. Nam?

720
00:44:19,130 --> 00:44:20,630
Are you getting this?

721
00:44:20,630 --> 00:44:22,230
Wait.

722
00:44:22,230 --> 00:44:26,000
What... Yes, we're getting you!

723
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:31,139
We're still getting static, so change the position you're in.

724
00:44:31,139 --> 00:44:33,979
Just a second.

725
00:44:35,080 --> 00:44:36,780
Darn it.

726
00:44:38,409 --> 00:44:40,180
Is this good enough?

727
00:44:41,619 --> 00:44:42,949
Are you still getting static?

728
00:44:42,949 --> 00:44:45,920
No, this is perfect. We hear you loud and clear.

729
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:47,389
We can hear you clearly.

730
00:44:47,389 --> 00:44:48,860
- Don't move from that spot.
- Sure.

731
00:44:48,860 --> 00:44:51,660
We can't afford to lose sound in here.

732
00:44:54,460 --> 00:44:56,099
What are you doing?

733
00:44:56,099 --> 00:44:57,830
Isn't it obvious?

734
00:44:59,069 --> 00:45:00,469
Move.

735
00:45:01,969 --> 00:45:03,739
I should join you.

736
00:45:04,539 --> 00:45:06,780
Guys, can you hear me?

737
00:45:06,780 --> 00:45:09,810
Yes, Officer Go. We hear you.

738
00:45:09,810 --> 00:45:12,610
Mr. Nam, Mr. Ma, good luck.

739
00:45:12,610 --> 00:45:17,750
That doesn't mean you can... I mean... You know...

740
00:45:17,750 --> 00:45:19,789
What are you getting at?

741
00:45:19,789 --> 00:45:22,460
I didn't lie down next to you because I wanted to.

742
00:45:22,460 --> 00:45:25,489
Hold on a second. Are you in bed together?

743
00:45:25,489 --> 00:45:27,699
You're supposed to be working!

744
00:45:27,699 --> 00:45:32,030
No, I meant that the phone was on its side.

745
00:45:32,030 --> 00:45:35,270
Don't drop it like that. Bring it up.

746
00:45:39,840 --> 00:45:41,809
- Mr. Cha.
- What?

747
00:45:41,809 --> 00:45:45,080
What is it?

748
00:45:45,080 --> 00:45:47,579
They're coming in.

749
00:45:47,579 --> 00:45:50,449
Right. Everyone, calm down.

750
00:45:50,449 --> 00:45:53,960
Mr. Nam with Lee Jonggu and Mr. Ma with Big Foot.

751
00:45:55,389 --> 00:45:56,980
Cheers!

752
00:45:57,659 --> 00:45:59,229
You did good work.

753
00:45:59,229 --> 00:46:02,630
I didn't know you'd be this proactive.

754
00:46:02,630 --> 00:46:05,469
A man should know when to strike.

755
00:46:05,469 --> 00:46:09,099
You're not wrong, since it only took one attempt.

756
00:46:09,969 --> 00:46:13,110
Gosh, that's good.

757
00:46:13,110 --> 00:46:14,740
Take your time with this.

758
00:46:14,740 --> 00:46:16,709
The drink is sweet on my lips.

759
00:46:16,709 --> 00:46:19,580
Let me see.

760
00:46:20,780 --> 00:46:24,450
One, two, three, four, five digits.

761
00:46:24,450 --> 00:46:28,420
You have the right amount.

762
00:46:30,330 --> 00:46:31,460
Is this where I sign?

763
00:46:31,460 --> 00:46:34,560
That's right. The money will be wired to you right away.

764
00:46:34,560 --> 00:46:35,559
Got it.

765
00:46:35,559 --> 00:46:37,599
Mr. Nam, let's ruin the deal for them.

766
00:46:37,599 --> 00:46:40,169
Have his pen make circles.

767
00:46:41,100 --> 00:46:43,740
What the...

768
00:46:44,339 --> 00:46:45,769
What is this?

769
00:46:45,769 --> 00:46:47,540
Is this your way of complaining about the amount?

770
00:46:47,540 --> 00:46:49,949
I don't know what's happening.

771
00:46:49,949 --> 00:46:52,349
Provoke him in a way that'll infuriate him.

772
00:46:52,349 --> 00:46:54,880
Infuriate him? Got it.

773
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:57,750
- What...
- What's going on?

774
00:46:57,750 --> 00:47:02,519
No, I'm not the one drawing on your face.

775
00:47:02,519 --> 00:47:05,659
- It isn't me.
- Are you nuts?

776
00:47:07,060 --> 00:47:09,259
Is it more money you want?

777
00:47:09,259 --> 00:47:12,330
Mr. Ma, scare him some more.

778
00:47:12,330 --> 00:47:13,940
- Mr. Nam, shall we?
- Sure.

779
00:47:13,940 --> 00:47:16,210
All right.

780
00:47:16,210 --> 00:47:18,069
- What the...
- What's wrong with me?

781
00:47:18,069 --> 00:47:19,369
Seriously?

782
00:47:19,369 --> 00:47:21,139
My arms are moving on their own.

783
00:47:21,139 --> 00:47:22,579
What is this?

784
00:47:22,579 --> 00:47:24,349
Are you into men?

785
00:47:24,349 --> 00:47:25,750
Well, I'm not!

786
00:47:25,750 --> 00:47:28,980
I'm not either. What on earth is wrong with me?

787
00:47:28,980 --> 00:47:31,320
- Did you put something in my drink?
- What?

788
00:47:31,320 --> 00:47:32,960
You spiked my drink to up the price.

789
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:34,589
Are you insane?

790
00:47:34,589 --> 00:47:38,059
You spiked the drink to cut me out of this deal!

791
00:47:38,059 --> 00:47:40,000
You twerp.

792
00:47:40,000 --> 00:47:43,300
I should've known that only a nutjob would kill his own wife.

793
00:47:43,300 --> 00:47:45,469
I have you on recording, you know.

794
00:47:45,469 --> 00:47:49,569
Play me in any way, and I'll feed you to the cops.

795
00:47:49,569 --> 00:47:51,310
You're one to talk.

796
00:47:51,310 --> 00:47:55,039
Weren't you the one... who suggested the thugs as fall guys?

797
00:47:55,039 --> 00:47:58,009
I have a recording of my own, too!

798
00:47:58,009 --> 00:48:01,119
- Nice. We got them.
- Yes!

799
00:48:01,119 --> 00:48:02,679
You can leave them be now.

800
00:48:02,679 --> 00:48:04,489
Just don't forget to bring the phone with you.

801
00:48:04,489 --> 00:48:07,019
- What?
- What the...

802
00:48:07,019 --> 00:48:09,960
I'd be a fool to come unarmed...

803
00:48:09,960 --> 00:48:11,330
when meeting a thug.

804
00:48:11,330 --> 00:48:14,960
I should never have done business with a con man.

805
00:48:14,960 --> 00:48:18,499
- Why you...
- Get over here.

806
00:48:20,540 --> 00:48:22,300
Drop your weapons!

807
00:48:23,369 --> 00:48:26,610
Lee Jonggu, Big Foot, surrender.

808
00:48:26,610 --> 00:48:28,509
The place is swarming with cops.

809
00:48:28,509 --> 00:48:31,650
Wait, it's Senior. What?

810
00:48:37,049 --> 00:48:38,549
Stop right there!

811
00:48:43,929 --> 00:48:45,729
Darn it.

812
00:48:50,429 --> 00:48:52,069
Darn!

813
00:49:06,049 --> 00:49:08,699
- Stop following me!
- Darn these stairs.

814
00:49:31,040 --> 00:49:33,410
That's 10,030, 10,031...

815
00:49:37,779 --> 00:49:41,280
And 10,033, 10,034, 10,035...

816
00:49:42,380 --> 00:49:47,219
And 10,035, 10,036...

817
00:49:48,719 --> 00:49:50,689
Stop right there!

818
00:49:51,759 --> 00:49:54,000
Come any closer...

819
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:55,699
and I'll jump.

820
00:49:55,699 --> 00:49:59,329
Go ahead. It'll make our job easier.

821
00:50:00,369 --> 00:50:04,369
Mr. Lee, this won't solve anything, so please come this way.

822
00:50:04,369 --> 00:50:07,539
Big Foot... He orchestrated everything.

823
00:50:07,539 --> 00:50:09,310
I only did as I was told.

824
00:50:09,310 --> 00:50:12,049
You call that an excuse? Enough with the nonsense.

825
00:50:12,049 --> 00:50:14,780
You clobbered your wife with a baseball bat!

826
00:50:14,780 --> 00:50:18,550
Mr. Lee, ignore this guy...

827
00:50:19,520 --> 00:50:21,320
and talk to me instead.

828
00:50:21,320 --> 00:50:23,759
I'm sure you had your reasons.

829
00:50:23,759 --> 00:50:29,659
I'll consider your situation and be understanding of your story,

830
00:50:29,659 --> 00:50:34,040
so please come this way and talk to me.

831
00:50:34,040 --> 00:50:36,440
She brought it on herself.

832
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:39,639
This wouldn't have happened had she listened to me.

833
00:50:39,639 --> 00:50:41,339
What did she do?

834
00:50:41,339 --> 00:50:45,110
The cow wouldn't listen, so, of course, I lost it!

835
00:50:59,659 --> 00:51:01,699
You killed her.

836
00:51:01,699 --> 00:51:04,170
She died because of you.

837
00:51:34,529 --> 00:51:37,059
Life was tough, wasn't it?

838
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:41,699
But you still managed to always do your best,

839
00:51:41,699 --> 00:51:44,769
so there aren't any regrets.

840
00:51:47,040 --> 00:51:48,339
Good.

841
00:51:50,350 --> 00:51:53,680
That's more than enough, Minsook.

842
00:52:01,860 --> 00:52:03,690
Thank you.

843
00:52:03,690 --> 00:52:07,999
I wouldn't have been able to move on without your help.

844
00:52:09,759 --> 00:52:12,630
You too, Mr. Grim Reaper. Thank you.

845
00:52:14,170 --> 00:52:16,839
Are you finally ready to leave?

846
00:52:18,139 --> 00:52:21,109
- Shall we?
- Hold on.

847
00:52:33,449 --> 00:52:35,089
Ms. Yoon,

848
00:52:36,790 --> 00:52:39,490
I will never forget...

849
00:52:40,130 --> 00:52:42,559
the kindness you showed me.

850
00:52:49,770 --> 00:52:52,439
I'll miss you so much.

851
00:52:59,949 --> 00:53:01,849
Officer Go,

852
00:53:01,849 --> 00:53:06,250
can I make a final request before I go?

853
00:53:06,250 --> 00:53:09,159
Yes, of course. It can be anything.

854
00:53:09,159 --> 00:53:13,900
The money I leave behind... will be spent on sponsoring the orphanage.

855
00:53:13,900 --> 00:53:15,929
I'm not worried about that at all.

856
00:53:15,929 --> 00:53:19,130
But could you drop in on the kids and see how they're doing...

857
00:53:19,130 --> 00:53:21,869
from time to time?

858
00:53:21,869 --> 00:53:24,139
Yes, of course.

859
00:53:24,139 --> 00:53:25,639
Don't you worry.

860
00:53:25,639 --> 00:53:27,339
Please look after them.

861
00:53:27,339 --> 00:53:32,110
Hyungsik, the eldest, will be of help being the smart boy he is.

862
00:53:32,110 --> 00:53:33,150
Good.

863
00:53:34,350 --> 00:53:37,950
And then there's Sangjun. He never eats his vegetables.

864
00:53:37,950 --> 00:53:39,420
Especially spinach and carrots.

865
00:53:39,420 --> 00:53:42,860
Please make sure he fixes his eating habits.

866
00:53:42,860 --> 00:53:46,230
And Daesung wishes to be a professional soccer player.

867
00:53:46,230 --> 00:53:48,630
Let him play outside if that's what he wants.

868
00:53:48,630 --> 00:53:50,699
He's not one to thrive academically.

869
00:53:50,699 --> 00:53:52,830
And then there is my pretty Daeun.

870
00:53:52,830 --> 00:53:56,500
She barely eats since her dream is to be a K-pop idol singer.

871
00:53:56,500 --> 00:53:59,539
She's just as skinny as Cha Chawoong.

872
00:53:59,539 --> 00:54:02,139
Make sure she eats well.

873
00:54:02,139 --> 00:54:04,349
My goodness.

874
00:54:04,349 --> 00:54:08,450
How can I leave them behind?

875
00:54:08,450 --> 00:54:11,819
[Mom, get well soon. From Daeun]

876
00:54:11,819 --> 00:54:13,389
All right.

877
00:54:14,119 --> 00:54:19,230
- Mr. Grim Reaper, let's go... before I change my mind.
- All right.

878
00:54:19,230 --> 00:54:23,230
Look at you getting ahead of yourselves.

879
00:54:23,230 --> 00:54:27,639
On whose authority will your money be spent on the orphanage?

880
00:54:27,639 --> 00:54:29,739
Just wait until I wake up.

881
00:54:29,739 --> 00:54:33,679
I'll sue you all... and receive my share of her money!

882
00:54:33,679 --> 00:54:36,580
According to the doctor, even if you do wake up,

883
00:54:36,580 --> 00:54:38,509
you'll be paralyzed from the neck down.

884
00:54:38,509 --> 00:54:39,580
What?

885
00:54:40,750 --> 00:54:45,449
Are you saying I'll have to be on my back forever?

886
00:54:45,449 --> 00:54:48,619
You darn fool!

887
00:54:48,619 --> 00:54:52,190
Why did you have to be so greedy when life is relatively short?

888
00:54:52,190 --> 00:54:56,260
When your time is up, you have to leave everything behind anyway.

889
00:54:56,260 --> 00:54:57,630
You should've listened to me.

890
00:54:57,630 --> 00:54:59,330
It was nonsense! Besides, it's my money...

891
00:54:59,330 --> 00:55:01,170
- As if. When I said...
- It wasn't your call to make!

892
00:55:01,170 --> 00:55:02,699
- That's nonsense!
- This is all your fault!

893
00:55:02,699 --> 00:55:04,710
- And I told you!
- You should've listened!

894
00:55:04,710 --> 00:55:07,509
Enough bickering!

895
00:55:07,509 --> 00:55:11,450
Let me do my job, darn it!

896
00:55:15,219 --> 00:55:17,219
Unbelievable.

897
00:55:17,219 --> 00:55:19,790
What do you need that for anyway?

898
00:55:19,790 --> 00:55:23,259
I must say the name on this list three times...

899
00:55:23,259 --> 00:55:28,330
for the body and soul to sever all ties.

900
00:55:28,330 --> 00:55:31,869
- Can't you be quiet and let me handle this?
- Sure.

901
00:55:46,819 --> 00:55:50,349
Lee Jonggu.

902
00:55:51,750 --> 00:55:53,150
Me?

903
00:55:54,619 --> 00:55:56,659
Lee Jonggu.

904
00:55:56,659 --> 00:56:00,959
What on earth? Why are you chanting my name, darn it?

905
00:56:03,630 --> 00:56:05,869
[Lee Jonggu | Death]

906
00:56:05,869 --> 00:56:12,139
Lee Jonggu!

907
00:56:15,509 --> 00:56:16,610
What on earth?

908
00:56:17,310 --> 00:56:20,510
Am I dead?

909
00:56:23,049 --> 00:56:24,590
Why?

910
00:56:25,389 --> 00:56:27,390
Why me?

911
00:56:29,759 --> 00:56:31,929
Read this yourself.

912
00:56:31,929 --> 00:56:34,899
The names have been switched.

913
00:56:34,899 --> 00:56:36,629
Let me see that.

914
00:56:38,600 --> 00:56:41,500
What about me, then?

915
00:56:41,500 --> 00:56:44,269
Mr. Grim Reaper, what about me?

916
00:56:44,269 --> 00:56:48,739
You can keep on living in this world.

917
00:56:48,739 --> 00:56:52,949
From what I hear, hundreds of petitions reached the Underworld.

918
00:56:52,949 --> 00:56:55,120
Petitions?

919
00:56:56,549 --> 00:57:00,820
From your children whom you never gave birth to.

920
00:57:02,920 --> 00:57:05,560
[I love you, Mama Minsook.]

921
00:57:06,529 --> 00:57:08,629
My puppies.

922
00:57:48,040 --> 00:57:51,340
That looks secure enough.

923
00:57:51,340 --> 00:57:55,880
To be honest, I've only heard rumors about such a thing happening.

924
00:57:55,880 --> 00:57:59,880
I guess this is what you call a miracle.

925
00:57:59,880 --> 00:58:03,750
I won't go with you. I can't!

926
00:58:03,750 --> 00:58:05,589
It's not something you can choose.

927
00:58:05,589 --> 00:58:09,159
Your fate has been sealed, so shut it.

928
00:58:09,159 --> 00:58:11,589
Anyway, I'll get going now.

929
00:58:14,830 --> 00:58:16,660
Thank you.

930
00:58:30,710 --> 00:58:33,579
Ms. Yoon, can you hear me?

931
00:58:40,690 --> 00:58:42,589
It's me, Seulhae.

932
00:58:42,589 --> 00:58:44,789
Do you recognize me?

933
00:58:53,029 --> 00:58:55,539
It really is a miracle.

934
00:58:59,909 --> 00:59:01,639
Chawoong...

935
00:59:02,710 --> 00:59:04,710
We did it.

936
00:59:05,909 --> 00:59:08,880
We brought her back to life!

937
00:59:08,880 --> 00:59:12,889
We did it. We brought her back!

938
00:59:16,819 --> 00:59:20,410
My gosh. Ms. Yoon is alive.

939
00:59:20,410 --> 00:59:26,590
 The light shines on you, us 

940
00:59:28,130 --> 00:59:33,940
 I'll be there even if you don't come 

941
00:59:35,920 --> 00:59:41,860
 Now, I'll wait 

942
00:59:49,119 --> 00:59:51,259
- That hurts.
- My apologies, sir.

943
00:59:51,259 --> 00:59:52,290
I'll lower the speed level.

944
00:59:52,290 --> 00:59:54,730
No, not there.

945
00:59:54,730 --> 00:59:58,570
Kicking the hacky sack 30,000 times qualifies as overdoing it.

946
00:59:58,570 --> 01:00:02,899
Exactly. It'll take four days to fully loosen your muscles.

947
01:00:02,899 --> 01:00:06,139
So much for stacking virtue power the easy way.

948
01:00:06,139 --> 01:00:09,310
Picking up after Chawoong is more exhausting.

949
01:00:09,310 --> 01:00:11,710
My body aches.

950
01:00:11,710 --> 01:00:15,179
What you did was commendable, sir.

951
01:00:16,150 --> 01:00:20,989
And 29,998, 29,999...

952
01:00:20,989 --> 01:00:23,319
Why must he go this far?

953
01:00:23,319 --> 01:00:26,289
- That's 30,000.
- Mr. Choi!

954
01:00:26,289 --> 01:00:28,289
We caught the culprit.

955
01:00:28,299 --> 01:00:31,190
Really?

956
01:00:31,190 --> 01:00:32,499
I'm glad.

957
01:00:36,869 --> 01:00:38,769
You...

958
01:00:38,769 --> 01:00:42,139
Was this all for that lady?

959
01:00:42,139 --> 01:00:46,079
Yes, she lived her whole life caring for others.

960
01:00:46,079 --> 01:00:49,320
I wanted her to have closure.

961
01:00:52,489 --> 01:00:54,960
So you kicked this 30,000 times to buy her time?

962
01:00:54,960 --> 01:00:57,789
Did he say 30,000?

963
01:01:01,190 --> 01:01:02,730
Gosh. You're something else.

964
01:01:20,880 --> 01:01:22,580
I admit my defeat.

965
01:01:24,320 --> 01:01:26,489
I'll leave now.

966
01:01:33,800 --> 01:01:35,800
Hyeonjoon.

967
01:01:39,799 --> 01:01:41,639
It was nice seeing you, my friend.

968
01:01:41,639 --> 01:01:43,500
You...

969
01:01:43,500 --> 01:01:46,010
are the best.

970
01:01:53,049 --> 01:01:55,580
Mr. Choi, you're sweating like crazy.

971
01:01:55,580 --> 01:01:57,419
Are you all right?

972
01:01:57,419 --> 01:01:59,320
My gosh. Just kill me.

973
01:02:01,659 --> 01:02:04,859
Oh, please. It was nothing.

974
01:02:06,060 --> 01:02:10,570
My chosen pupil should be the one seeing this.

975
01:02:10,570 --> 01:02:13,769
Where on earth is he at?

976
01:02:26,280 --> 01:02:29,019
- What are you having?
- Gosh.

977
01:02:38,889 --> 01:02:40,689
How nice.

978
01:02:43,099 --> 01:02:45,400
Millet shell makgeolli?

979
01:02:45,400 --> 01:02:46,869
Where did you get this?

980
01:02:46,869 --> 01:02:49,969
Head Yoon gave it to me as a token of her gratitude.

981
01:02:49,969 --> 01:02:53,470
And you were hoarding it all for yourself?

982
01:02:55,039 --> 01:02:57,080
Let's drink.

983
01:03:08,619 --> 01:03:12,260
I can't believe I spent ten years not drinking this.

984
01:03:12,260 --> 01:03:13,759
What a waste of my life.

985
01:03:13,759 --> 01:03:14,829
Hold on.

986
01:03:14,829 --> 01:03:18,569
Why would you stop drinking... these drops of paradise for ten years?

987
01:03:18,569 --> 01:03:22,800
It was Sageum's favorite.

988
01:03:22,800 --> 01:03:29,379
Whenever we wanted to celebrate, we'd enjoy it together.

989
01:03:30,309 --> 01:03:34,320
But then you ran away from home,

990
01:03:34,320 --> 01:03:37,080
and he quit drinking.

991
01:03:41,490 --> 01:03:43,559
Blood sure is thicker than water.

992
01:03:43,559 --> 01:03:48,760
Just like your grandfather, you're crazy over makgeolli.

993
01:03:49,530 --> 01:03:52,129
Would he have felt this way, too?

994
01:03:53,530 --> 01:03:59,070
There's this odd feeling I get after helping people, you see.

995
01:04:02,010 --> 01:04:06,249
It's as if I'm comforting my own soul.

996
01:04:06,249 --> 01:04:08,479
Would he...

997
01:04:09,619 --> 01:04:12,389
have felt this way, too?

998
01:04:15,420 --> 01:04:19,829
Listening to others and offering them solace...

999
01:04:19,829 --> 01:04:25,460
sometimes leads to yourself being comforted.

1000
01:04:27,170 --> 01:04:29,620
Is that why they make it their mission?

1001
01:04:31,240 --> 01:04:35,540
First Grandpa and now Officer Go.

1002
01:04:37,350 --> 01:04:41,720
It's the way of life as a member of society.

1003
01:04:43,719 --> 01:04:48,059
That is why we must have a companion...

1004
01:04:48,059 --> 01:04:50,959
in life and around a drink table.

1005
01:04:52,529 --> 01:04:53,889
Here.

1006
01:05:08,909 --> 01:05:10,809
Gosh, that's good.

1007
01:05:12,280 --> 01:05:16,280
It doesn't taste as good as it did the first time.

1008
01:05:16,280 --> 01:05:17,589
What could be missing?

1009
01:05:17,589 --> 01:05:19,090
Food, of course.

1010
01:05:19,090 --> 01:05:21,719
- Here's your tofu and kimchi.
- Get in here.

1011
01:05:21,719 --> 01:05:23,790
What are you doing pairing it with cheese?

1012
01:05:23,790 --> 01:05:25,589
- Of course.
- You also need some green onion pancakes.

1013
01:05:25,589 --> 01:05:28,360
- Absolutely.
- Green onion pancakes it is.

1014
01:05:28,360 --> 01:05:31,130
Hold on. Where did this come from?

1015
01:05:31,130 --> 01:05:33,130
Mr. Choi told us to order it.

1016
01:05:33,130 --> 01:05:35,770
Stop taking credit for what you buy with my money!

1017
01:05:35,770 --> 01:05:38,469
It's the company's, not yours.

1018
01:05:38,469 --> 01:05:41,610
All right. Why waste a perfectly good chance, right?

1019
01:05:41,610 --> 01:05:43,940
We might as well party since we have food anyway!

1020
01:05:43,940 --> 01:05:45,349
Yes, a team dinner!

1021
01:05:45,349 --> 01:05:47,210
- Here.
- Mr. Choi, let me pour you a glass.

1022
01:05:47,210 --> 01:05:48,350
Isn't this our first team dinner?

1023
01:05:48,350 --> 01:05:49,920
Of course. Mr. Nam, have a glass.

1024
01:05:49,920 --> 01:05:51,619
- Sure.
- Goodness.

1025
01:05:51,619 --> 01:05:54,089
Mr. Cha, you too.

1026
01:05:55,860 --> 01:05:57,020
Mr. Choi, please say a toast.

1027
01:05:57,020 --> 01:05:59,060
All right. Cheers!

1028
01:05:59,060 --> 01:06:01,699
- Cheers.
- He said, "Cheers."

1029
01:06:01,699 --> 01:06:03,259
Bring it in.

1030
01:06:03,259 --> 01:06:06,170
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

1031
01:06:09,239 --> 01:06:11,440
Gosh, that's good.

1032
01:06:11,440 --> 01:06:14,280
Yes, keep on pouring.

1033
01:06:14,280 --> 01:06:17,579
Mr. Cha, bottoms up.

